title: Recipe Rating Prediction
description: This data science project conducted at UCSD explores the factors influencing recipe ratings using a dataset from food.com. Specifically, this project investigates how various recipe nutrients, like calories and total fat, contributes to a recipe's rating. By analyzing these features, our project aims to explore viewer preferences of nutrition levels of highly-rated recipes and develop a predictive model for recipe ratings.

title: Youtube Comments Generation
description: Generate Youtube comments using a transformer model. The model is trained on a dataset of Youtube comments and can generate new comments based on a given prompt. The generated comments can be used for various purposes, such as improving engagement on Youtube videos or generating fake comments for testing purposes.

title: FPro Scores across Stores and Price Ranges
description: Created visualizations using FPro scores across different stores and price ranges. The visualizations help to understand how FPro scores vary across different stores and price ranges, and can be used to identify trends and patterns in the data.

title: Deceptive Visualizations
description: Created two visualizations that are persuasive to both sides of the proposition. The visualizations are designed to be misleading and can be used to demonstrate how visualizations can be manipulated to support different arguments. The project aims to raise awareness about the potential for deception in visualizations and the importance of critical thinking when interpreting data.
